African National Congress (ANC) President Cyril Ramaphosa reflected on the party’s achievements since the dawn of democracy. He addressed the ANC’s gala dinner at Durban’s Inkosi Albert Luthuli International Convention Centre, ahead of the party’s election manifesto launch on Saturday  Earlier, ANC Head of Campaigns Fikile Mbalula says volunteers are on the ground to mobilise communities for an ANC victory. He was speaking at the start of the ANC Manifesto Preview Dinner in Durban on Friday evening. Business people, senior party members including former President Jacob Zuma as well as representatives of fraternal parties from Angola’s MPLA, Mozambique’s Frelimo and Zimbabwe’s Zanu-PF attended the dinner. Mbalula says unity will be central in their election manifesto campaign. Fikile Mbalula , Related video click below: